Package uintTesting

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Date
    The Date class holds the date in mm/dd/yyyy
    DateTest
    The DateTest class tests that the isValid() method works correctly.
    International
    The International is a subclass of NonResident that can have a student study abroad
    InternationalTest
    The InternationalTest class tests that the tuitionDue method in International by calling it then accessing it through getTuitionFee() and checking that the amounts line up to where it should.
    NonResident
    The NonResdident is a subclass of Student that cannot have financial aid
    Person  
    Profile
    The Profile class holds name, major, and fulltime of a student we'll use the profile in
    Resident
    The Resident class is a subclass of Student that has the ability to have financial aid
    Roster
    The Roster class will hold a list of students and let the user manipulate the list with methods
    RosterTest
    The RosterTest class tests that the add() and remove() methods works correctly.
    RunProject2
    The RunProject2 class calls the TuitionManager to start the program.
    Student
    The Student class holds the information of a student and declares some methods that will be used in subclasses
    TriState
    The TriState is a subclass of NonResident that can have a discount based on the state the student live in
    TuitionManager
    The TuitionManager class runs from Project2's main method and is the interface for commands of roster.
